                <h1>The Evolution of Animal Testing: A Historical Overview</h1>
                <p>The history of animal testing dates back thousands of years, with early civilizations using animals for medical research. In the 19th century, ethical concerns arose, prompting regulations. The 20th century saw significant advances in technology, reducing reliance on animals. Today, the debate continues over the necessity and ethics of animal testing in science.</p>
